{"title_page": "Amal Karunasekara", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox military person\n|honorific_prefix = [[Major-General (Sri Lanka)|Major General]]\n|name= Amal Karunasekara\n|image= \n|image_size= \n|caption= \n|birth_date=\n|death_date= \n|birth_place= \n|death_place= \n|placeofburial= \n|nickname= \n|allegiance= Sri Lanka\n|branch= {{army|Sri Lanka}}\n|serviceyears= 1981 \u2013 2018\n|rank= [[Major-General (Sri Lanka)|Major General]]\n|unit=[[Sri Lanka Light Infantry]]\n|commands= Chief of Staff<br/>[[Security Forces Headquarters \u2013 Kilinochchi|Kilinochchi Security Forces]]<br/>[[53 Division (Sri Lanka)|53 Division]]<br/>Sri Lankan Contingent, [[United Nations Stabilisation Mission in Haiti]] \n|battles= [[Sri Lankan Civil War]]<br/>[[1987-89 JVP Insurrection (Sri Lanka)|Insurrection 1987-89]]\n|awards= [[File:Rana Wickrama Padakkama Bar.png|20px]] [[Rana Wickrama Padakkama]]<br> [[File:Rana_Sura_Padakkama_bar.GIF|20px]] [[Rana Sura Padakkama]] <br>[[File:Vishista Seva Vibhushanaya medal bar.svg|20px]] [[Vishista Seva Vibhushanaya]]<br>[[File:Uttama Seva Padakkama Bar.gif|20px]] [[Uttama Seva Padakkama]]\n|laterwork= \n}}\n\n[[Major-General (Sri Lanka)|Major General]] '''K.A.D. Amal Karunasekara''', [[Rana Wickrama Padakkama|RWP]], [[Rana Sura Padakkama|RSP]], [[Vishista Seva Vibhushanaya|VSV]], [[Uttama Seva Padakkama|USP]], [[General Sir John Kotelawala Defence University|ndu]], [[Psc (Military)#Sri_Lanka|psc]] was a senior Sri Lankan army officer and 51st Chief of Staff of the [[Sri Lanka Army]].<ref name=\"Appointment\">{{cite web|url=http://newsfirst.lk/english/2017/07/major-general-amal-karunasekara-appointed-new-chief-staff-sl-army/170765|title=Major General Amal Karunasekara appointed Army chief of staff|website=newsfirst.lk|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref> \n\n==Education==\nEducated at [[Nalanda College Colombo]], Karunasekara was a Senior Cadet in the school's [[National Cadet Corps (Sri Lanka)|cadet platoon]]. Having received his basic training at the [[Sri Lanka Military Academy]], he is a graduate of the [[Defence Services Command and Staff College]], the [[Defence Services Staff College]] and the [[PLA National Defence University]] having studied Defence and Stretegic Studies. He also holds a [[Master of Science|MSc]] in Defence and Strategic Studies from the [[University of Madras]]; and a [[Master of Science|MSc]] in Defense Management from [[General Sir John Kotelawala Defence University]]<ref name=\"Appointment\" />.\n\n==Military career==\nKarunasekara enlisted in the [[Sri Lanka Army]] as an [[Officer Cadet]] in 1981, going on to earn his commission as a [[Second Lieutenant]] in the [[Sri Lanka Light Infantry]] after completing training at the [[Sri Lanka Military Academy]], [[Diyatalawa]] in 1984<ref name=\"asiantrib\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asiantribune.com/node/90742|title=Major General Amal Karunasekara - New Chief of Staff of Sri Lanka Army|website=Asiantribune.com|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref>. Over the next 35 years, he would rise through the ranks of the army, holding such key positions as Director Military Intelligence, Director Infantry, Master General of Ordnance Branch, and Military Secretary<ref name=\"asiantrib\" />.  Karunasekara has held both battalion- and brigade-level commands during the [[Eelam War IV|Eelam War]], and has commanded the [[53 Division (Sri Lanka)|53 Division]] during its course<ref name=\"asiantrib\" />. In addition, he was appointed the commander of the Sri Lankan contingent of the [[United Nations Stabilisation Mission in Haiti|UN peacekeeping mission in Haiti (MINUSTAH)]] when first deployed in 2004<ref name=\"asiantrib\" /><ref name=\"Haiti\">{{cite web|url=http://www.loophaiti.com/content/ses-soldats-la-minustah-ont-viole-des-enfants-il-est-promu|title=Ses soldats \u00e0 la Minustah ont viol\u00e9 des enfants, il est promu|website=loophaiti.com|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref>. \n\nHe was the 15th [[Colonel#Colonel_of_the_Regiment|Colonel of the Regiment]] of the [[Sri Lanka Light Infantry]] regiment, having occupied this position once temporarily between 2007 and 2009<ref name=\"asiantrib\" />. He was an instructor at [[Sri Lanka Military Academy|Diyatalawa]] and Directing Staff at the [[Defence Services Command and Staff College]].\n\nKarunasekara was appointed Commander of Security Forces Headquarters- Kilinochchi on 18 October 2015; he was promoted to Chief of Staff of the Army on 22 July 2017, after the promotion of [[Mahesh Senanayake]] to [[Commander of the Army (Sri Lanka)|Army Commander]] earlier the same month left the position vacant<ref name=\"asiantrib\" />. He retired from service on 14 March 2018 with the rank of [[Major General]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Army Chief of Staff Maj. Gen. Karunasekara retires|url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/article/Army-Chief-of-Staff-Maj-Gen-Karunasekara-retires-147253.html|accessdate=27 March 2018|agency=Daily Mirror|publisher=dailymirror.lk|date=14 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Controversy==\nAs commandant of the Sri Lankan contingent of [[United Nations Stabilisation Mission in Haiti|MINUSTAH]] since 2004, Karunasekara has been at the center of the [[Sexual abuse scandal in Haiti|child sexual abuse scandal]] that troops and officers under his command have been implicated in<ref name=\"Haiti\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/080330/News/news0015.html|title=UN confirms sex charges|website=Sundaytimes.lk|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 April 2018, he was arrested by the [[Sri Lanka Police]] [[Criminal Investigation Department (Sri Lanka)|Criminal Investigation Department]] on charges of aiding and abetting the abduction and assault on [[The Nation (Sri Lanka)|The Nation]] journalist Keith Noyahr in 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Keith Noyahr abduction: Rtd. Major General Karunasekara arrested|url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/article/Keith-Noyahr-abduction-Rtd-Major-General-Karunasekara-arrested-148325.html|accessdate=5 April 2018|agency=Daily Mirror|publisher=dailymirror.lk|date=5 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"noyahrColPage\">{{cite news|title=Retired senior Sri Lankan Army officer arrested for attack on journalist|url=http://www.colombopage.com/archive_18A/Apr05_1522934388CH.php|accessdate=5 April 2018|agency=ColomboPage|publisher=colombopage.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fmr. Military Intelligence Chief Arrested|url=http://www.hirunews.lk/187741/fmr-military-intelligence-chief-arrested|accessdate=5 April 2018|agency=Asia Broadcasting Corporation|publisher=Hiru News}}</ref> Karunasekara was accused of being part of a group of military intelligence operatives that functioned under the direction of the [[Mahinda Rajapakse]] government between 2006 and 2010.<ref name=\"noyahrColPage\"/> He is currently under investigation for several related acts of state-sanctioned violence, including the assassination of [[Lasantha Wickrematunge]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Arrest of Sri Lanka\u2019s ex-military intelligence chief leads to breakthrough|url=http://economynext.com/Arrest_of_Sri_Lanka%E2%80%99s_ex_military_intelligence_chief_leads_to_breakthrough-3-10304.html|accessdate=6 April 2018|agency=EconomyNext|publisher=economynext.com|date=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKarunasekara is married, and has one daughter with his wife Dananjanie<ref name=\"asiantrib\" />. \n\nHaving been an avid hockey player at school level, he has represented Sri Lanka at national level in the sport and has gone on to be chairman of the Sri Lanka Army Hockey Committee<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.army.lk/news/engineers-corps-wins-inter-regiment-hockey-championship|title=Engineers Corps Wins Inter Regiment Hockey Championship|website=army.lk|accessdate=24 July 2017}}</ref> <ref>[http://www.army.lk/news/51st-army-chief-staff-assumes-office 51st Army Chief of Staff Assumes Office]</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n<br>\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mahesh Senanayake]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chief of Staff of the [[Sri Lanka Army]]|years=July 2017 - March 2018}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Dampath Fernando]]}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karunasekara, Amal}}\n[[Category:Sri Lankan Buddhists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Nalanda College, Colombo]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sri Lanka Light Infantry officers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox military person\n|honorific_prefix = [[Major-General (Sri Lanka)|Major General]]\n|name= Amal Karunasekara\n|image= \n|image_size= \n|caption= \n|birth_date=\n|death_date= \n|birth_place= \n|death_place= \n|placeofburial= \n|nickname= \n|allegiance= {{flag|Sri Lanka}}\n|branch= {{army|Sri Lanka}}\n|serviceyears= 1981 \u2013 2018\n|rank= [[Major-General (Sri Lanka)|Major General]]\n|unit=[[Sri Lanka Light Infantry]]\n|commands= Chief of Staff<br/>[[Security Forces Headquarters \u2013 Kilinochchi|Kilinochchi Security Forces]]<br/>[[53 Division (Sri Lanka)|53 Division]]<br/>Sri Lankan Contingent, [[United Nations Stabilisation Mission in Haiti]] \n|battles= [[Sri Lankan Civil War]]<br/>[[1987-89 JVP Insurrection (Sri Lanka)|Insurrection 1987-89]]\n|awards= [[File:Rana Wickrama Padakkama Bar.png|20px]] [[Rana Wickrama Padakkama]]<br> [[File:Rana_Sura_Padakkama_bar.GIF|20px]] [[Rana Sura Padakkama]] <br>[[File:Vishista Seva Vibhushanaya medal bar.svg|20px]] [[Vishista Seva Vibhushanaya]]<br>[[File:Uttama Seva Padakkama Bar.gif|20px]] [[Uttama Seva Padakkama]]\n|laterwork= \n}}\n\n[[Major-General (Sri Lanka)|Major General]] '''K.A.D. Amal Karunasekara''', [[Rana Wickrama Padakkama|RWP]], [[Rana Sura Padakkama|RSP]], [[Vishista Seva Vibhushanaya|VSV]], [[Uttama Seva Padakkama|USP]], [[General Sir John Kotelawala Defence University|ndu]], [[Psc (Military)#Sri_Lanka|psc]] was a senior Sri Lankan army officer and 51st Chief of Staff of the [[Sri Lanka Army]].<ref name=\"Appointment\">{{cite web|url=http://newsfirst.lk/english/2017/07/major-general-amal-karunasekara-